  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I'd like to have more control over my chat history and want to delete it anytime.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Currently, it's unclear how long the chat history is stored. The minimal requirements are to have an ability to delete it completely. \r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n*Summary*: \r\n- From a chat, a user can tap \"more\" then \"Clear chat\". This will keep the chat but delete its contents.\r\n- This applies to 1-to-1,group-chat and public chats alike.\r\n- Old messages will not be received again\r\n\r\nFuture idea:\r\nA more advanced option would be to set a timer when chat history should be deleted or delete it if the session is ended (definition of the session also needs to be developed or specified).\r\n\r\nSplit from https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/3988 by @adambabik \r\n",
